  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Lord, who throughout these forty days For us didst fast and pray, Teach us with Thee to mourn our sins And close by Thee to stay.",
    "v2": "As Thou with Satan didst contend, And didst the vict&#39;ry win, O give us strength in Thee to fight, In Thee to conquer sin.",
    "v3": "As Thou didst hunger bear, and thirst, So teach us, gracious Lord, To die to self, and chiefly live By Thy most holy Word.",
    "v4": "And through these days of peni- tence, And through Thy passiontide, Yea, evermore in life and death, Jesus, with us abide.",
    "v5": "Abide with us, that so, this life Of suff&#39;ring over past, An Easter of unending joy We may attain at last."
  },
